724813f-a.title: Manhattan: William Street - Spruce Street
724813f-a.text:
(1)
william Street, west side, (left), at Spruce Street (right), shozing
the 9-story Press Club building at the N.W.cor. Buildings on the left, are
Ngs. 183 to 179 William Street, at, adjoining and south of the S.W. corner
of Spruce Street. On the right are shown Nos. 23, 25 and 27 Spruce
Street, at and adjoining the N.E. corner of William Street. Note excawa-
tion work at the S.E. corner of the two streets, and the Municipal Build-
ing in the far background.
December 18, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(2)
The same, another view, showing the Beekman Street (fower left)
side of the excavation.
December 18, 1930.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
(3)
The same, at a later date, showing a comprehensive view of the
Press Club building. Note the site of excavation being used as an
automobile parking space.
January 20, 1932.
P. L. Sperr.
NO REPRODUCTIONS.
